Ghost Chat

A private real-time chat application with secure rooms, passphrase protection, and live presence tracking.

Features

Private rooms with custom room keys
Join rooms using a passphrase
Persistent user identity (no need to re-enter name)
Auto rejoin last room after refresh
Real-time messaging using Firebase
Online / Offline status with last seen
Clean dark UI

Tech Stack

Frontend: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
Backend: Firebase Realtime Database
Session Handling: LocalStorage

Project Structure

ghost-app/

index.html
css/style.css
js/app.js
js/rooms.js
js/chat.js
js/call.js
js/firebase.js
js/crypto.js
js/ui.js

How to Run

Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_REPO.git
Go into project
cd ghost-app
Install Firebase CLI
npm install -g firebase-tools
Login
firebase login
Deploy
firebase deploy --only hosting

Live Demo

https://ca-imp-questions.web.app

How It Works

Each user gets a unique persistent userId
Rooms are stored using roomId
Members are tracked using userId (prevents duplicates)
Presence is handled using Firebase onDisconnect

Limitations

Passphrase stored locally (not fully secure)
No end-to-end encryption yet
No file/media sharing

Future Improvements

Message seen and delivered ticks
Voice and video calling
End-to-end encryption
Invite links / QR join
Better UI animations

